No one party is responsible for the challenges in our #education system, but we all share the responsibility of addressing them #Jordan
Challenges # Education is intertwined; no one is responsible for the problem, but we are all responsible for solving it
The most important lesson we have learned from His Majesty is that the shortest route to resolve a problem is by confronting it
The most important thing that His Majesty has taught us is that the shortest way to solve problems is confrontation, not ignorance
Success is within reach if we invest in #education today ... the only thing standing btw our present and the future we aspire to is ourselves
Success is at our disposal if we invest in education, today .. not tomorrow .. not stand between our present and the future we aspire to but ourselves
Jordanians have, time and again, shown that if they want to achieve something, they can; and we want quality #education for our children
Jordan # was not described as a land of torque. Jordanians have proven repeatedly that if they wanted to ... they did. We want a quality education for our children
Let us equip our schools with technology and e-learning tools so that our children become fluent in the language of the century #Jordan
We want our children to work in the 21st century, so we can provide our schools with e-learning tools to make our students free in the language of the age of Jordan
We want a curriculum that enriches learning, so let us establish a Curriculum Center to develop and modernize what we teach our children #Jordan
We want curricula that enrich education and open the horizons of knowledge. Let us establish a specialized center to follow the latest educational methods and to develop and update curricula
We want qualified teachers, so we're establishing a teacher #education college to train them for a year before they enter the classroom
We want qualified teachers ... so we are collaborating today to create a teacher training college and train them for a year before entering the # classes of education
#Education reform must be a national priority and a public demand today, tomorrow and ten years from now #Jordan
# Education must be a national priority and popular demand today .. and tomorrow after ten years # Jordan
